 Discover 5 unique access control devices.

Access control devices are used to restrict and manage entry to physical or digital spaces, ensuring only authorised individuals can gain access.
1. Keypad Door Lock
Proof: see Fig22
Observation:
A keypad lock requires users to enter a PIN to unlock the door.

2. RFID / Access Card System
Proof: See Fig13
Users tap a card on a reader to gain access.

3. Biometric Fingerprint Scanner
Proof: See Fig21
Observation:
While at work, each employee needs to punch in using their fingerprint to start their work. 

4. Security Turnstile (Card + Gate System)
Proof: See Fig20
Observation:
